Document: VisualShaderNodeBooleanConstant
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodebooleanconstant.rst
Summary: A shader node that outputs a boolean value with no input ports.

This class represents a boolean constant in the visual shader graph. It has only one output port and no input ports. The node is translated to the `bool` type in the shader language. It is used to represent fixed boolean values (true/false) within shader programs, providing a way to hardcode boolean conditions directly into the visual shader network.
